When you get a request, do you receive one per matter or can one email cover multiple matters? Often one email is per matter. However, in the case of property settlements, you might receive multiple deposits for different matters on the same day. In those cases you’d need attachments or rows on the form to specify which deposit applies to which matter.

We handle multiple rows per deposit. The paperwork needs to be provided for each matter so there’s proper supporting evidence. Even if one payment covers multiple matters, the one-to-one relationship between matter and allocation must be maintained in the record.

If a request comes in and the actual payment amount differs from the expected amount, we handle that by closing the request and expecting a second payment, or capturing the change in the record. That reconciliation between expected and actual amounts should be captured in ServiceNow so we have an audit trail.

We’d like the ServiceNow form to provide a PDF record and to be able to store notes and time-stamped audit entries. We need readable, auditable records that auditors can review. Time stamps are important — the created date and the audit trail entries should be included in exported PDFs.

